title: Chicken Simulator
description:
Not a glitch:
1. Can't buy a seed when you have enough eggs
It's not that the game thinks you don't have enough, but charlie is in the coop and you can't feed her until she gets out of the coop and she's not already eating something. If it still doesn't work, then it is a glitch.


2. Nothing happened when the bug is clicked
This is also because charlie is laying an egg, wait for her to finish then she can eat, the bug follows the cursor, she won't eat it until she is touching it

3. Mood won't increase/decrease
It changed in the hidden "mood" variable. The facial expression just didn't change.

4. Charlie won't go to the coop
Charlie won't go to the coop if you've just bought a seed, and won't go until the food is given to her

Credits:
art taken from internet
The egg is from Minecraft
(Woulda included sources but twelve year old ytarie5 was freaking dumb and didn't bother)
used a text engine from @Jirachi7593
Song is from duck life
I made basically everything else
instructions:
Only advertise remixes of this project or projects similar to this one. Scroll for instructions vvv

Instructions:
Every now and then, charlie the chicken will go into the coop and lay an egg, the smiley face determines charlie's mood. The more the mood drops (It drops fast!), the slower she lays eggs. To boost her mood, you must feed her seeds. A seed costs 5 eggs (They're converted to their value in money before you buy it before you ask) and it will follow your mouse pointer, just drag it to her. If you're low on eggs to buy seeds, occasionally a bug will fly by. You can click on it to feed her. There is a hidden "egg rate" variable (hidden as in there being no way to see your current egg rate normally, it's not really meant to be secret...), this changes how many eggs she will lay at the same time; the game will not tell you when it changes, but you can tell what it is if you pay attention to how many eggs your chick is laying at a time (Maybe I'll add a "ding!" sound when it changes in the future?). There is a 20% chance of the "egg rate" rising when fed a bug (there is no other way to raise it).

title: Virtual Chicken Coop
description:
Welcome to the most realistic chicken coop simulator on scratch, currently featuring 10 different breeds of chickens!

Featured! Yay! :D

UPDATES-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

I've added a button that allows you to hide/show chickens to make it easier to collect eggs when you have a lot of chickens. ;)  It also looks a little weird when the chickens are invisible and eggs appear in the nest... O.o

ABOUT--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Build your own flock of chickens starting with one! Collect eggs to earn coins and buy more chickens! Purchase a rooster to hatch chicks! Earn achievements and upgrade your coop with more nests and room for more birds! Collect the rarest breeds and varieties!

GLITCHES-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

If you experience a glitch, please comment and I will attempt to fix it. In the meantime, try going to the shop, waiting five seconds, and then exiting. In theory, that should temporarily fix any glitches.

Known Glitches:

-Double Cloning: Lots of chickens appear after leaving the shop. 
I switched the cloning of chickens to a different sprite, instead of         the chicken sprite...hopefully that fixes this.
-The Return of the Black Pancake: A strange black blob appears instead of chicks. I've made a few changes, so it might be fixed now.
-The Return of the White Pancake: Cochin eggs turn into white pancakes. I think I've fixed it! ;)

CREDITS------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Sounds from the scratch library.
Art, etc. @b00k_w0rm

This game has been featured before. 

Press the green flag, then click either:

START:
   It presets the chicken to look like a Plymouth Rock chicken. Click anywhere to change how your chicken looks, then, click the save button to get your save code. Press space to hide the save code.

LOAD: 
   If you have copied a save code, press ctrl+v at the same time to paste it. Press enter, and there it is!

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

TO  COPY A SAVE CODE:
   Highlight the numbers with your mouse, until they're all blue. Press ctrl+c to copy it. Now, you can share your chicken with everyone!
   To paste, press ctrl+v. Feel free to post you code in comments!

title: Hungry Little Chicken
description:
It was my mom who gave an idea to make such a game. My dad drew all the graphics and helped me develop scripts. We used a Russian Traditional melody "Fried Chicken" for the background music.
FEATURED! Surprisingly and unexpectedly... Thank you, Scratch! You ask why and how? So do I. If you have some thoughts how to improve the game and make it more interesting, feel free to remix it!
And have a look on my other games. They are cool and funny too.
instructions: A little chicken has just hatched. She is very hungry. In the wide world around her, there are worms crawling, ants running and bees flying. Feed her. Press Left and Right to move the chicken, Space to peck. Each worm gives you 5 score, each ant 10 score. But beware bees. Don't peck when one is around or the bee stings you. Four stings take a life. The game ends successfully when you get 1000 score! Good luck.

title: Iron Chicken 3D - Point animation
description:
The original Runold was here:
http://scratch.mit.edu/projects/24828817

v0.1 Gun is unreliably loaded but rather fallible on the animation front.
v0.2 Colours stored in a list - suggestions appreciated, remembering I now use the colour/shade method
v0.3 Experimenting with the internal lists and the 3D view - feel free to adjust and let me know!
v0.4 Multiple sprites used for the animation, semi-successfully
v0.5 Experiments in triangles and hidden fields - not perfect but getting there.
v0.6 Hidden fields gone, speed increase done with point animation
v0.7 More hidden field experimentation - it now has solid areas, though not as we know it...
v0.8 The lasers are now working. You are limited to 6 shots before a reload. I don't see why the machine fires backwards sometimes though.
v0.9 Sorting out timing and speed, which is seems to be a major problem in fact.
v0.10 Walking being worked on, hence why he currently 'hops' in a very peculiar manner!
v0.11 It walks, though the 'knees' are not entirely convincing. Must look at my trigonometry...
v0.12 Parking installed.
v0.13 Now featured, fields included to display the lines / dots and hidden fields
v0.14 Cloning removed on the joints code, now done purely with lists
v0.15 Perspective problems resolved, AKA the lasers are now working properly!
v0.16 Sorting finally managed using a quicksort routine giving a perfect sort and the potential for no clones
v0.17 Colours now stored using RGB method (thanks @WO997!)
instructions:
This was based on the Runold 3D engine which has successfully animated some earlier characters of mine.

For instructions, look under the 'i' on the bottom-left of the screen.
